The `memory` tool does **not emit any telemetry per operation**.

Looking at its function definition, the `memory` tool supports six commands (`view`, `create`, `str_replace`, `insert`, `delete`, `rename`) that operate on two scopes:

- **`/memories/project/...`** — repo-specific knowledge (conventions, hard-won findings, dead-ends)
- **`/memories/global/...`** — cross-project preferences

Each operation simply reads from or writes to persistent note files. There is no mention of telemetry, analytics, metrics collection, or any external data emission in the tool's specification. The tool is designed as a local, persistent key-value-style note system for the agent to retain knowledge across sessions.
